The paper deals with deep multi-task networks for autonomous driving systems, which involves computer vision (CV) and machine learning (LG) techniques. The focus is on optimizing the performance of the network for multiple tasks, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (AI). The application domain is autonomous driving systems, which involves robotics (RO) and systems and control (SY). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV and cs.LG, followed by cs.RO, cs.AI, and cs.SY.
